Recently I found after reload `script classes`, the original `script classes` didn&#39;t get unloaded. The reason is when creating a new thread, it will hold a new context object(see `java.lang.Thread`):
```
this.inheritedAccessControlContext =
                acc != null ? acc : AccessController.getContext();
```
So If a `script class` is created by such a thread, the object will hold the `ScriptClassLoader` object used to load the `script class`, causing this `ScriptClassLoader ` to be unable to be GC and thus unable to unload useless `script classes`.

The gc root strace:
```
